      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Earnest money is held in escrow to protect both parties, ensuring that if the deal falls through for any reason, that money can be used to cover damages or penalties. If the inspection reveals major foundation issues, you have a few options, and it depends entirely on what your contract says and what you both agree to. It's a very important time to have a good, thorough inspection, or you'll be stuck with those big problems later on.",
