    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so the escrow agent is kinda like a neutral middleman then? i just want to make sure they aren't just sitting on the money for no reason. like, what exactly is their job during this whole process? are they just holding it or do they actually do stuff with it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow agent is definitely a neutral middleman, a crucial figure in the transaction, much like a trusted broker who keeps track of all the moving parts. They aren't just sitting on the money; they are actively managing the funds, ensuring that the earnest money is only released under very specific, agreed-upon conditions outlined in your contract. They are responsible for verifying documents, coordinating inspections, and making sure all the money moves the right way.",
